# Official Docs & API Verification

Reference docs for: Expo, React Navigation, Redux Toolkit, Supabase,
NativeWind, React Hook Form.

| Library | URL |
|---------|-----|
| Expo | https://docs.expo.dev |
| React Navigation | https://reactnavigation.org/docs/getting-started |
| Redux Toolkit | https://redux-toolkit.js.org/introduction/getting-started |
| Supabase | https://supabase.com/docs |
| NativeWind | https://www.nativewind.dev/overview |
| React Hook Form | https://react-hook-form.com/get-started |

## Before using any API from these libraries

- Check the installed version in `package.json` / lockfile — do not assume
  the latest docs match the installed version.
- If unsure whether a method/hook/prop exists at the installed version,
  search the actual docs or check `node_modules/.../*.d.ts` — never guess
  from training data, which may describe a different major version.
- If a Context7 MCP or equivalent docs-fetch tool is available, prefer it
  over memory for anything touching Supabase RLS syntax, RTK Query
  cache invalidation, or Expo SDK-specific APIs — these have changed
  multiple times across recent versions and are the most common source
  of subtly broken code.
- If you cannot verify an API confidently, say so and propose the safer
  known-working alternative rather than shipping a guess.
